						               													<description>Translated from the German introduction:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Dear parents, Ich spiele Einkaufen shall support children playfully to develop a better understanding of the numbers and quantities from 1-5. The vocabulary can be expanded as well. For this discuss all items on the shopping lists and the names of the shops repeatedly. Since there are regional differences in naming the goods and shops just use the one most appropriate to you.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Ich spiele Einkaufen is a children's game which shall help to develop competence in the number range 1-5. Each player is given a list with 5 different items on it in 5 different amounts (1-5) which need to be gathered from 5 different shops.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game map shows the different shops (3 times each) as well as a supermarket where you can get every good and 3 spots without any action. A 6 sided die numbered from 1-4 (1&amp;amp;2 are doubled) is rolled and the number is advanced on the shops track around the board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If the player ends on a shop where he needs some good from he can claim it by naming the good and the amount of it (e.g. &amp;quot;I take 5 sausages from the butchery&amp;quot;). The player then picks the needed item token from the map and places it on his/her shopping list. The first player to collect all 5 items from the shopping list wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
